In a large saucepan over high heat, bring stock, garlic and tomatoes to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Cool slightly before pur√©eing half of soup in a food processor or blender until smooth. Repeat with remaining soup. Return to saucepan. Add basil and reheat to serving temperature. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Fresh Tomato Basil Variation: Replace canned tomatoes with 6 large peeled and diced tomatoes. Add 1/4 cup (50 mL) tomato paste during the cooking and follow method using all ingredients.